Eight people were yesterday killed while seven others sustained injuries as a result of suicide bomb attacks in villages of Konduga Local Government Area of Borno State. The state police spokesman, DSP Edet Okon, said in a statement issued in Maiduguri at about 12.04am, four suicide bombers detonated IEDs strapped to their bodies in Mainari-Kanuri and Mainari-Shuwa villages in Konduga LGA. “Three of them detonated the IEDs killing themselves, while the fourth person killed herself and three others,” he said, adding, “Seven other persons were injured and have been evacuated to the hospital. Security has also been beefed up in the area and all around Maiduguri Metropolis.” He added that on Thursday in Bama, a suicide bomber was sighted by security agents and was promptly neutralized. No casualty was recorded.